title: For Sale:  Ruger Lyman Centennial
postcontent: In 1980 or thereabouts, Ruger Firearms collaborated with Lyman rifle scopes to produce a presentation rifle/scope combination to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the Lyman rifle scopes.  The rifles were beautifully stocked Ruger No 1's chambered in 45-70, paired with a replica of the original, long, skinny rifle scope that Lyman started with.  The pair are presented in a fitted walnut case with reloading dies, cleaning rod, and a book on the history of Lyman corporation.  Only 1000 of these sets were produced.  I acquired this set in about 1985.  To my knowledge it has never been fired.  There are a few minor scratches on the walnut case, but otherwise the set is mint.
